t somehow, the job makes sense when it\\u2019s done. It fits the context of the organization, but can\\u2019t be explained outside of it. You become specialized, but not like the factory worker is specialized. You don\\u2019t spend your whole day putting one piece of a widget together. Knowledge workers do more than one thing, but those things might not have any obvious relationship with each other. Your job is cobbled together filling in some of the skill gaps that a team has. \"\n      })]\n    }), /*#__PURE__*/_jsx(\"footer\", {\n      children: \"\\xA9 Andrew Bryant\"\n    })]\n  });\n}","map":null,"metadata":{},"sourceType":"module"}